<h2>ðŸ”“ Stealer Logs - By Email</h2>

<p>Find which website domains appear in stealer logs for a given email address.</p>

<div class="info">
  <strong>Note:</strong> This feature requires a Pwned 5+ subscription and verified domain ownership.
</div>

<form method="post" action="/stealer-logs-email">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="email">Email Address:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="user@example.com" required>
  </div>

  <button type="submit">Search Stealer Logs</button>
</form>

<% if defined?(@error) %>
  <div class="error">
    <strong>Error:</strong> <%= @error %>
  </div>
<% end %>

<% if defined?(@success) && @success %>
  <div class="result success">
    <h3>Stealer Log Domains for <%= @email %></h3>

    <% if @result.empty? %>
      <p>âœ… No stealer log entries found for this email.</p>
    <% else %>
      <p>This email appears in stealer logs for <strong><%= @result.length %></strong> domain(s):</p>

      <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
        <% @result.each do |domain| %>
          <span class="badge badge-danger"><%= domain %></span>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <h4 style="margin-top: 30px;">Raw JSON Response:</h4>
    <pre><%= JSON.pretty_generate(@result) %></pre>
  </div>
<% end %>

<div class="info" style="margin-top: 30px;">
  <h3>About Stealer Logs</h3>
  <p>Stealer logs are databases of credentials stolen by information-stealing malware. They contain usernames, passwords, and cookies harvested from infected devices.</p>
  <p>Finding credentials in stealer logs indicates they were actively stolen from a compromised device.</p>
</div>
